         <abstract>
            <p>To estimate a multiple integral of a function over the unit cube, Haber proposed two Monte Carlo estimators $J'_1$ and $J'_2$ based on $2N$ and $4N$ observations, respectively, of the function. He also considered estimators $D^2_1$ and $D^2_2$ of the variances of $J'_1$ and $J'_2$, respectively. This paper shows that all these estimators are asymptotically normally distributed as $N$ tends to infinity.</p>
          </abstract>
